{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Ambient data methods infer inertia from naturally occurring load fluctuations, though they often struggle with measurement noise [5].",
    "Probing signal techniques [6] offer improved control and observability, but their deployment is intrusive and costly.",
    "Event-based estimation methods [7], those that leverage frequency response data from actual disturbances, have gained traction as a practical and accurate alternative.",
    "These event-based methods capture how the system responds under stress, including contributions from all sources of inertial response, whether synchronous or nonsynchronous.This paper contributes a practical and scalable methodology for estimating regional inertia using real-world frequency data from Frequency Monitoring Network (FNET/GridEye).",
    "Unlike prior studies [5], [7] that focused on interconnection-wide study, our approach explicitly focuses on regional dynamics."
  ],
